[A] Point out the errors, if any, in the following C statements:

(a) x = (y + 3);
Error : No error.

(b) cir = 2 * 3.141593 * r;
Error : No error.

(c) char = '3';
Error : Variable name should not be keyword.

(d) 4/3 * 3.14 * r * r * r = vol_of_sphere;
Error : Variable should not be in right side.

(e) Volume = a^3;
Error : Exponential operation can be done by pow function.

(f) area = 1/2 * base * height;
Error : No error.

(g)si = p * r * n / 100;
Error : No error.

(h) areaofcircle = 3.14 * r  * r;
Error : No error.

(i) peri_of_tri = a + b + c;
Error : No error.

(j) slope = (y2 - y1) .-.(x2 - x1);
Error : Division operation is performed by / operator.

(k) 3 = b = 4 = a;
Error : Assignment operator cn be assigned one left side and right side.

(l) count = count + 1;
Error : No error.

(m) char ch = '25Apr12'
Error : Only one character can be assigned to a single character variable.

